The paper focuses on the problem of script identification in scene text images, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed method involves the use of ensembles of networks, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also proposes a new benchmark dataset for the evaluation of multi-lingual scene text end-to-end reading systems, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
